==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic, cognate with Old Frisian ''blīd-'', Old Saxon [[bliþi|blīþi]] (Dutch [[blijde]]), Old High German [[blidi|blīdi]], Old Norse [[blíðr]], Gothic [[𐌱𐌻𐌴𐌹𐌸𐍃]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'bli:ðe/

===Adjective===
'''blīþe'''
# [[clement]], [[gentle]]
#:''Wese us beorhtnes ofer bliðan Drihtnes ures'': let the brightness of our gentle Lord be over us.
# [[glad]], [[happy]]
#:''Wæs Iethro bliðe for eallum ðam þingum, ðe Drihten dyde Israhela folce'': Jethro was glad for all the things the Lord did for the people of Israel.

